node_modules is where all project dependencies live, including react library
public is all the files that are public to the browser, all the react component(e.g. App.js) will be injected to index.html file under <div id='root'>, 
src has all react components, app.js is a sample component, index.js is what kick starts our app, it will take <App /> component and render it inside document.getElementById('root')


index.js -> app.js -> (navbar.js & home.js & create.js & BlogDetails.js)
                                    |
                                bloglist.js
                                    |
                                BlogDetails.js

npx json-server --watch data/db.json --port 8000
npm run start